narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A great chance to get course credit for a project you want to work in with an E&EB prof!
If you have any interest in research, take the year-long approach: you'll get more done and get a better feel for what it's like to "do" science...
I would definitely recommend this course to another student. It was relatively easy and really interesting to pursue my own research.
Yes if you want to do research for a summer.

It can be rewarding if you find a interesting project and a supportive lab. My advice is to start writing the paper early, and to understand as much about the project as you can in the early stages so you know what you're doing.
Yes. You'll know if its for you!
